The paper focuses on sound event detection using deep learning models, which falls under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SD). The integration of Non-Negative Matrix Factorization (NMF) with Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) is a novel approach that involves matrix factorization and neural networks, which could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of CNNs for feature extraction and classification is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV), which could also be applicable in this paper. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of data and the investigation of the types of data required to achieve the best performing system, which could be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR).
